OL,4,Ca baby in broad daylight
OL,6,FGoldrick was jailed for 12 months at
OL,7,FPreston Crown Court today after
OL,8,Fadmitting her guilt. A restraining
OL,9,Forder was also made for five years.
OL,11,FTom Snape, Senior Crown prosecutor for
OL,12,Fthe Crown Prosecution Service North
OL,13,FWest, said: "Nicolette Goldrick's
OL,14,Fbrazen actions caused unimaginable
OL,15,Fterror as she attempted to abduct a
OL,16,Fbaby.
